<h1> Avalanche Method</h1>

<h3>
    In the Avalanche method, the strategy is to organize all debts from highest interest rate amount due to lowest.  First attack the debt with the highest interest rate amount until it is gone, 
    and then focus on the next largest interest rate debt.  Remember you are still responsible to make the minimum payments on each of the other debts along the way.
</h3>


<h3>
    Let's say for example you have three debts to pay, Student Loan at $23,674 with an interest rate of 4.27%, Medical Bill at $12,813 with an interest rate of 4.9%, and 
    Car Loan at $19,985 with an interest rate of 5%.  Using the Avalanche method the first thing you would do is to organize the debt interest rate amounts from greatest to least.
</h3>



