<h3>
    The Car Loan has the greatest overall interest rate.  Your goal is to get rid of that debt as soon as possible, because the higher interst rate is costing you more money.  
    While making the minimum payments on the Medical Bill and the Student Loan, you will also make EXTRA payments on the Car Loan.  Your extra payment may only be $5 over the 
    minimum amount, that's ok.  Pay as much as you can in extra based on your income.  Once the Car Loan is paid off, move on to attacking the Medical Bill with extra payments.
</h3>

<h3>The Avalanche methood focuses on saving you money in interest payments.  Paying off the highest interest rate first will save more money than paying the lower interest rates off first.  </h3>

